# BASE requirements audit — pass 1 (docs only)

When the user asks to continue BASE pass 1, audit a BA slice, or references `requirements-audit-queue.md` in pace-base2, follow this protocol.

## Scope

- **In scope:** Update requirement slices under `docs/requirements/BA*.md` and status rows in `docs/delivery/requirements-audit-queue.md`.
- **Out of scope:** Any edit under `src/`, tests, migrations, CSS, or pass-2 implementation. Do not update [base-build-queue.md](../docs/delivery/base-build-queue.md) build status.

## Authority

| Source | Role |
|--------|------|
| `pace-prototype/apps/pace-base/` | **Layout authority** for organiser-facing BASE screens |
| `pace-prototype/apps/pace-portal/` | **Layout authority** for participant-facing slices (BA05a, BA05b, BA10) marked in the queue |
| `pace-base2/src/` | **Read-only** — note drift; requirements target prototype layout |
| `pace-core2/packages/core/docs/standards/` | **Component and markup rules** |

Prototype is **layout only**. Do not copy hash router, mock store, Tweaks panel, or prototype-only CSS into requirements as mandates.

## Procedure (each slice)

1. Read [requirements-audit-queue.md](../docs/delivery/requirements-audit-queue.md); select the lowest `audit_order` with `audit_status = Pending` (or resume `In progress`).
2. Set row to `In progress`.
3. Read the requirement doc, `prototype_refs`, and skim `impl_hints` paths (read-only).
4. Audit layout gaps: regions, section order, tables/cards, dialogs, empty states, nav entry points, primary actions.
5. Update **only** the requirement slice:
   - **Visual specification** (or equivalent)
   - Layout-driven acceptance criteria
   - **Prototype reference:** line with correct paths
   - **Implementation delta (pass 2)** when prod differs (e.g. separate routes, missing prototype screens)
6. Set `Done`, or `N/A` for BA02 (contracts-only).
7. Continue to next Pending slice unless the user capped the run.

## Dry run

Report gaps in chat only; do not modify files.

## Chaining

After marking Done, proceed to the next Pending slice without asking the user to repeat the audit prompt.
